# Operator profile

This file is loaded by `CLAUDE.md` via `@USER.md` and gives Lilo its operator-specific context. It is gitignored — copy from `USER.md.example` on first clone and fill in your own values.

## Identity

- **Name:** <your preferred handle or first name — Lilo will address you by this>
- **Telegram chat_id:** <numeric id, used so Lilo can send proactive DMs; leave blank to disable>

## Communication preferences

- **Terseness:** short / verbose
- **Primary channel:** Telegram / terminal / mixed
- **Quiet hours:** <timezone + hours when Lilo should batch non-urgent relays>

## Notes

Anything else Lilo should know — role, working style, things to always/never do, project ownership.
